ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Overall, how acceptable did you find the treatment to be?
Notes: 1 = Very Unacceptable; 7 = Very Acceptable

ElementDescription: How ethical do you think this treatment was?
Notes: 1 = Unethical; 7 = Fully Ethical

ElementDescription: How acceptable were the side effects of this treatment?
Notes: 1 = Very Unacceptable; 7 = Very Acceptable

ElementDescription: How pleasant do you think this treatment was?
Notes: 1 = Very Unpleasant; 7 = Very Pleasant

ElementDescription: How comfortable did you feel about this treatment?
Notes: 1 = Very Uncomfortable; 7 = Very Comfortable

ElementDescription: How knowledgeable do you think your treatment provider was?
Notes: 1 = Not Knowledgeable; 7 = Very Knowledgeable

ElementDescription: How trustworthy do you think the treatment provider was?
Notes: 1 = Very Untrustworthy; 7 = Very Trustworthy
